Last week Josphat Muoga was poisoned at Miomponi in Tigania West, Meru. His brother John Mutirithia said they were taking alcoholic in an illicit brew den when he was poisoned. He alleged another man was poisoned at Kwa Ng'ombe recently. But Tharaka South OCPD Walter Obondo,ondling the matter said they have arrested some suspects as investigations are ongoing. On July 3, Meru County Commissioner (CC), Wilfred Nyagwanga regretted over the high number of murder cases stating that a day barely ends without murder being reported. 